	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I was wondering what the proven method is for slowing planes mobs.  I made my first visit to PoN last night and noticed that those mobs really really (did I mention really?) hate being slowed.  In the beginning, I was slowing immediately after the melees engaged.  Almost every time, the mob went straight for me.  Then I figure I'll wait until the mobs take some damage and the MT generates a decent amount of aggro before I slow.  Well, the group didn't like that idea because the cleric was always oom by the time the fight was over.  So, I went back to slowing immediately and taking a few hits every fight.  This of course, made it more difficult on the MT to maintain aggro.  Oh, and we had SK's in group, so I had their neat little anti-aggro buff on me the whole time.  Thoughts on this?<br />
<br />
Secondly, if my slows were resisted, the chanter in the group would land his slow.  Is my slow so much better than a chanter's that I should still try to get my slow to stick even after they land theirs (overwriting their slow)?<br />
<br />
Thanks!</p>
	
	
	
