	<p>Hail,<br />
<br />
Here's how I do it.  It isn't perfect, it probably isn't even smart sometimes, but it works for me when grinding exp.  Raid mini-bosses or named are handled differently.  This method requires Torpor &amp; Malo to be effective.<br />
<br />
Preparation:<br />
Two simple hotkeys setup to /assist Puller &amp; /assist Maintank.<br />
I force the puller to announce his/her incoming.  "Inc %t" is all I really need.<br />
<br />
Action:<br />
1.  On the incoming mesage, I hit my puller assist key.  I spam click it until a target shows up in window.<br />
1a. If the puller announces adds or is intentionally pulling multiples, I automatically cast Torpor on myself at this point.  (Torpor is hotkeyed with a "Torporing %t" message btw.)<br />
<br />
2.  Spam click Malo until the mob is in casting range.  The aggro on this is extremely mild, and if it is a warrior tanking, his arrow shots on incoming will overcome the Malo aggro.  (If the warrior didn't bring arrows &amp; the group has no access to free ones, expect to have initial aggro.)  With Paladin/SK tanks, this isn't even an issue.  <br />
<br />
3.  Cast Slow with Turgur's as soon as your gems refresh.  Note, on most pulls, this will have Turgur's landing or resisting right as the mob enters the camp.  With a good paladin/SK tank, the aggro still goes right to them if slow lands the first try because they are stunning, casting Darkness, etcetera on the mob as it is incoming as well.<br />
<br />
4.  Towards the middle or end of casting Turgur's (step 3), /pet attack.  Sending in the dog at this point will generally position him on the opposite side of the tank, which is what I want so he avoids enrage damage, and saves the tank from having to flip (which they generally won't do just for a shaman pet anyway).<br />
<br />
(If slow is resisted, I go one of two routes, usually dependent on the tank's class &amp; my trust in the primary healer.)<br />
<br />
5a.  With a Warrior tanking, I Torpor myself before casting Turgur's again.  (While casting Torpor, I announce slow was resisted x1.)<br />
5b. With a Pal/SK tanking, I cast Turgur's ASAP again.  Recast up to a 3rd time &amp; then Torpor self.  I announce all slows resisted.  "resist x2, resistx3, I'm dead now," etc. <img src="images/smilies/biggrin.gif" border="0" alt="" title="big grin" smilieid="4" /><br />
<br />
I'm sitting at around 4400-4600hp buffed most of time while exp grinding w/ AC buffed anywhere around 1070-1150, so nothing uber, but good enough to get the job done.  This is enough to be able to tank most Tier1 or 2 mobs (while Torpored) for the period of time before aggro shifts.  Unless slow resists more than twice, I generally never require ANY outside healing.  <br />
<br />
It takes some time to train the pick-up primary healers NOT to heal me unless they see "resists" in /gsay.  Some never learn.  But most clerics &amp; druids eventually see the light.  Torpor w/ SCR3, SCRM, &amp; 8th shawl is an extremely efficient HoT.<br />
<br />
Take care,</p>
	
	
	
