	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Another thing you can do to minimize the agro you gain from the mobs is to place yourself in close proximity to the MT.<br />
In my case I dual box my 65 warrior and 62 Shammy all the time and I find if I position my Shaman within melee range I rarely ever get hit, and If I do it isnt for very long before the warrior regains the agro.<br />
My tactics are the same as the above poster: I malo on incomining hitting my hotkey as soon as possible and once the mob is in range it goes off. This enables me to cast my slow as soon as my gems refresh getting the slow on the mob as soon as possible. Slowing ASAP is important in PoP as the mobs do so much more damage.<br />
By Positioning my Shaman close to the melee if I do get agro ( i dont always ) I find 90% of the time the warrior regains agro immediately because he doesnt have to run around looking for where the mob went too.<br />
Try it, it works.<br />
<br />
Naralli Ironsmith<br />
65 warlord VoLS<br />
the rathe</p>
	
	
	
	
	
